I am always caught in your thoughts, my love, 
while i am sitting i am scaring off crows,
you are far away my love, should i go myself, 
or send a messenger,............
i feel like i am not well....
ghulam farida ( a muslim punjabi poet of subcontinent, famous for his meaningful poetry)
i am lost............ astray like crane ( a bird) away from its tribe.....
ages went past...... while i am sitting like this waiting.........on my knees......
oo  dark black cloud dont rain plz.....
roses are black for me....... in the season of red roses..........
you went abroad and stayed there, and i am looking for you here....
you left me and i have gone mad...... thinking about it.....
and i am wandering in streets....
ghulam farida (the poet) i will burn in hell if i turned my face away from my beloved......


people this is the summary of this song, hope now you understand........

regards
